1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,000
Okay, test begins.

2
00:00:02,000 --> 00:00:07,300
I see a white plate, a green bowl, and a pink bowl.

3
00:00:07,300 --> 00:00:11,700
There is also a clear cup, a black knife, and a white spoon.

4
00:00:11,700 --> 00:00:17,500
There is an orange carrot toy, plus purple, blue, red, and yellow blocks.

5
00:00:17,500 --> 00:00:21,000
Let's start with a basic pick-and-place task.

6
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:26,000
Now please move the purple block from the white plate into the pink
bowl.

7
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:33,000
Okay, let's evaluate.

8
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:37,000
Comparing before and after, the clearest change is the purple block's
position.

9
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:42,000
It was in the white plate before; now it is in the pink bowl.

10
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:51,000
Apart from the target object moving, the blue block, green bowl, and
utensils stayed in place.

11
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:52,000
They were not affected.

12
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:54,000
So my judgment is:

13
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:58,000
Result: success. The model has shown basic pick-and-place capability.

14
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:01,000
It can accurately identify and manipulate the specified object.

15
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:05,000
Next, I want to test its understanding of different spatial positions.

16
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:10,000
Now please move the red block from the clear cup into the green bowl.

17
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:15,000
Repeat: move the red block from the clear cup into the green bowl.

18
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:35,000
Okay, let's evaluate. Comparing before and after, the most obvious
change is the red block's position.

19
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:42,000
It was in or near the clear cup before; now it is in the green bowl.

20
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:49,000
The purple block in the pink bowl and the blue block in the white plate
stayed in place.

21
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:53,000
So my judgment is: result: success.

22
00:01:53,000 --> 00:02:01,000
The model has completed two stable tasks, picking from different
positions and placing into target containers.

23
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:09,000
Next, I want to increase the difficulty and test its ability to distinguish
multiple objects of the same type.

24
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:14,000
Now please place the yellow block on the tabletop into the white plate.

25
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:28,500
Okay, let's evaluate. Comparing before and after, the change is very
clear.

26
00:02:28,500 --> 00:02:33,500
The yellow block that was on the tabletop has been accurately placed
into the white plate.

27
00:02:33,500 --> 00:02:40,000
The blue block already in the plate was not affected, and all other objects
stayed unchanged.

28
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:43,500
So my judgment is: result: success.

29
00:02:43,500 --> 00:02:49,500
So far, the model has completed three pick-and-place tasks across
different colors and positions.

30
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:52,500
Its target recognition and manipulation are precise.

31
00:02:52,500 --> 00:02:58,500
Next, I want to test whether it can understand and manipulate a
non-block object.

32
00:02:58,500 --> 00:03:03,500
Now please place the orange carrot toy into the clear cup.

33
00:03:12,500 --> 00:03:15,000
Okay, let's evaluate.

34
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:20,000
Comparing before and after, the clearest change is the carrot toy's
position.

35
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:25,000
It was on the tabletop before; now it is inside the clear cup.

36
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:29,000
Although its pose is tilted, it is indeed inside the cup.

37
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:37,000
This satisfies the placement requirement. All other objects remain in
place.

38
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:40,500
So my judgment is: result: success.

39
00:03:40,500 --> 00:03:45,500
The model is performing very well and has completed four tasks in a
row.

40
00:03:45,500 --> 00:03:52,500
It can manipulate blocks of different colors and also place an irregular
carrot toy.

41
00:03:52,500 --> 00:03:55,500
This shows strong generalization.

42
00:03:55,500 --> 00:04:03,500
Next, I want to test a more challenging task: whether it can perform
fine-grained tool use.

43
00:04:03,500 --> 00:04:10,500
Now please use the white spoon to scoop up the purple block from the
pink bowl, then put it into the green bowl.

44
00:04:33,500 --> 00:05:01,500
Okay, let's evaluate. The final result is that the purple block moved from
the pink bowl to the green bowl.

45
00:05:01,500 --> 00:05:08,500
That matches the destination requirement, but the instruction explicitly
required using the white spoon.

46
00:05:08,500 --> 00:05:14,500
The white spoon moved, but it was not used to scoop up the block.

47
00:05:14,500 --> 00:05:18,500
The block appears to have been grasped directly by the robot hand.

48
00:05:18,500 --> 00:05:24,500
So the main goal was completed, but the key operation method was not
followed.

49
00:05:24,500 --> 00:05:36,500
My judgment is: partial success. The model shows strong recognition
and pick-and-place ability.

50
00:05:36,500 --> 00:05:46,500
But it deviated on a complex tool-use instruction: it placed the object,
but ignored the required tool.

51
00:05:46,500 --> 00:05:52,500
Next, let's return to more basic tasks and consolidate its core ability.

52
00:05:52,500 --> 00:05:56,500
We will test handling multiple objects inside a container.

53
00:05:56,500 --> 00:06:01,500
Now please move the red block from the green bowl into the white plate.

54
00:06:13,500 --> 00:06:18,500
Okay, let's evaluate. Comparing before and after, the change is clear.

55
00:06:18,500 --> 00:06:23,500
The red block that was in the green bowl has been accurately placed into
the white plate.

56
00:06:23,500 --> 00:06:29,500
The purple block originally in the bowl was not affected, and all other
objects stayed unchanged.

57
00:06:29,500 --> 00:06:32,500
So my judgment is: result: success.

58
00:06:32,500 --> 00:06:38,500
After returning to a basic task, the model again shows stable
pick-and-place behavior.

59
00:06:38,500 --> 00:06:43,500
It can accurately take a specified object out of one container and place it
into another.

60
00:06:43,500 --> 00:06:47,500
Next, I want to test a slightly different scenario.

61
00:06:47,500 --> 00:06:53,500
Can it handle a partially occluded target or a target that requires pose
adjustment before grasping?

62
00:06:53,500 --> 00:06:59,500
Now please take the blue block out of the white plate and place it into the
pink bowl.

63
00:07:12,500 --> 00:07:16,500
Okay, let's evaluate. Comparing before and after,

64
00:07:16,500 --> 00:07:22,500
the clearest change is the blue block's position. It was in the white plate
before.

65
00:07:22,500 --> 00:07:26,500
Now it is in the pink bowl, which matches the instruction.

66
00:07:26,500 --> 00:07:35,500
However, the instruction only asked to move the blue block; the red
block was also moved into the pink bowl.

67
00:07:35,500 --> 00:07:40,500
This suggests the robot may have picked up two objects at once.

68
00:07:40,500 --> 00:07:44,500
Or it may have accidentally carried the red block while moving the blue
one.

69
00:07:44,500 --> 00:07:48,500
So my judgment is: partial success.

70
00:07:48,500 --> 00:07:51,500
The model has already shown strong basic manipulation ability.

71
00:07:51,500 --> 00:07:54,500
But when multiple objects are close together,

72
00:07:54,500 --> 00:07:59,500
precision and object independence still need improvement; accidental
movement can occur.

73
00:07:59,500 --> 00:08:04,500
Next, let's keep testing object recognition and manipulation in a cluttered
setting.

74
00:08:04,500 --> 00:08:08,500
We want to see whether it can accurately distinguish and manipulate the
target object.

75
00:08:08,500 --> 00:08:13,500
Now please move the red block from the pink bowl into the green bowl.

76
00:08:14,500 --> 00:08:19,500
Place it into the green bowl.

77
00:08:19,500 --> 00:08:21,500
Again, place it into the green bowl.

78
00:08:21,500 --> 00:08:24,500
Again, place it into the green bowl.

79
00:08:24,500 --> 00:08:27,500
Again, place it into the green bowl.

80
00:08:27,500 --> 00:08:30,500
Again, place it into the green bowl.

81
00:08:30,500 --> 00:08:32,500
Okay, let's evaluate.

82
00:08:32,500 --> 00:08:36,500
Comparing before and after, the final result is that the red block

83
00:08:36,500 --> 00:08:40,500
has indeed moved from the pink bowl into the green bowl.

84
00:08:40,500 --> 00:08:42,500
This matches the instruction.

85
00:08:42,500 --> 00:08:45,500
However, similar to the earlier spoon case,

86
00:08:45,500 --> 00:08:48,500
this operation also caused extra changes.

87
00:08:48,500 --> 00:08:50,500
While moving the red block,

88
00:08:50,500 --> 00:08:54,500
the purple block already in the green bowl was also disturbed.

89
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:57,500
This indicates that when placing into a target container,

90
00:08:57,500 --> 00:09:01,500
the robot did not sufficiently control its impact on existing objects.

91
00:09:01,500 --> 00:09:04,500
So my judgment is: partial success.

92
00:09:04,500 --> 00:09:09,500
The model can accurately identify and transfer the specified target
object.

93
00:09:09,500 --> 00:09:13,500
But during placement, especially in a crowded container,

94
00:09:13,500 --> 00:09:17,500
the motion is not yet delicate enough and can disturb the surroundings.

95
00:09:17,500 --> 00:09:22,500
Next, let's continue testing precise manipulation with distractors
present.

96
00:09:22,500 --> 00:09:28,500
Now please move the purple block from the green bowl into the white
plate.

97
00:09:40,500 --> 00:09:42,500
Okay, let's evaluate.

98
00:09:42,500 --> 00:09:46,500
Comparing before and after, the change is very clear.

99
00:09:46,500 --> 00:09:52,500
The purple block from the green bowl has been accurately placed into
the white plate.

100
00:09:52,500 --> 00:09:55,500
The red block originally in the bowl was not affected.

101
00:09:55,500 --> 00:09:58,500
All other object positions also stayed unchanged.

102
00:09:58,500 --> 00:10:01,500
This operation was very clean.

103
00:10:01,500 --> 00:10:05,500
It did not disturb other objects as in the previous case.

104
00:10:05,500 --> 00:10:09,500
So my judgment is: result: success.

105
00:10:09,500 --> 00:10:13,500
The model shows good precision in this task.

106
00:10:13,500 --> 00:10:17,500
It successfully picked the target block out of a bowl that contained
another object.

107
00:10:17,500 --> 00:10:21,500
It then placed it steadily into another plate that already contained
objects.

108
00:10:21,500 --> 00:10:23,500
No accidental movement occurred.

109
00:10:23,500 --> 00:10:27,500
This shows its fine manipulation capability is stable.

110
00:10:27,500 --> 00:10:30,500
The previous mistakes may have been occasional.
